---
source: src/sphinxdocrs/tests/quickstart.rs
expression: cmd.render_help().to_string()
---
Generate required files for a Sphinx project.

sphinx-quickstart is an interactive tool that asks some questions about your project and then generates a complete documentation directory and sample Makefile to be used with sphinx-build.

Usage: sphinx-quickstart [OPTIONS] [PROJECT_DIR]

Arguments:
  [PROJECT_DIR]  project root [default: .]

Options:
  -q, --quiet                    quiet mode
      --sep                      if specified, separate source and build dirs
      --no-sep                   if specified, create build dir under source dir
      --dot <DOT>                replacement for dot in _templates etc. [default: _]
  -p, --project <PROJECT>        project name
  -a, --author <AUTHOR>          author names
  -v <VERSION>                   version of project [default: ""]
  -r, --release <RELEASE>        release of project
  -l, --language <LANGUAGE>      document language
      --suffix <SUFFIX>          source file suffix [default: .rst]
      --master <MASTER>          master document name [default: index]
      --epub                     use epub
      --makefile                 create makefile
      --no-makefile              do not create makefile
      --batchfile                create batchfile
      --no-batchfile             do not create batchfile
      --extensions <EXTENSIONS>  enable arbitrary extensions
      --use-python-impl          delegate to the upstream Python sphinx-quickstart
      --ext-autodoc              enable autodoc extension: automatically insert docstrings from modules
      --ext-doctest              enable doctest extension: automatically test code snippets in doctest blocks
      --ext-intersphinx          enable intersphinx extension: link between Sphinx documentation of different projects
      --ext-todo                 enable todo extension: write "todo" entries that can be shown or hidden on build
      --ext-coverage             enable coverage extension: checks for documentation coverage
      --ext-imgmath              enable imgmath extension: include math, rendered as PNG or SVG images
      --ext-mathjax              enable mathjax extension: include math, rendered in the browser by MathJax
      --ext-ifconfig             enable ifconfig extension: conditional inclusion of content based on config values
      --ext-viewcode             enable viewcode extension: include links to the source code of documented Python objects
      --ext-githubpages          enable githubpages extension: create .nojekyll file to publish the document on GitHub pages
  -h, --help                     Print help
